# Creating Placement Groups

## Introduction
In this post, we'll walk through the steps to create Placement Groups and launch instances within them, ensuring optimal resource utilization and application performance.
---

## Steps to create a placement Groups

### 1. Log in to AWS Management Console
1. Navigate to the [AWS Management Console](https://aws.amazon.com/console/).
2. Log in with your credentials.

---

### 2. Create Placement Group
1. On the left hand pane, scroll down and choose placement groups option under network and security.
![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/36cc6f73-a3ba-4993-8842-dcdaef1f1db6)
2. Click on  create a placement group.
![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c7b5eebe-f92c-4589-966a-45bdcc05b564)
3. Enter the name of your placement group.
![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0f0ab813-2da2-48fb-8b85-219c2771f2f7)
4. Choose the placement strategy
![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0f0ab813-2da2-48fb-8b85-219c2771f2f7)
5. Click create placement groups

---

### 3. launching an instance in a placement group.
1. click on launch instances.
2. Scroll down, and under the advanced details, you can locate the settings for placement group name.
![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6800e828-7152-4e05-b5e8-267fd8ee4f28)
3. Select the name of your placement group.
4. click on launch Instance
